==English==

===Etymology===
Contraction of ''[[whore]]'' and ''[[son]]'', or the son of a whore.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)sən|-ɔː(r)sən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an illegitimate child born of unwed parents.
#:*'''1605''': Though this knave came something saucily to the world before he was sent for, yet was his mother fair, there was good sport at his making, and the '''whoreson''' must be acknowledged. — William Sakespeare, ''King Lear'' I.i
# (literal) the son of a [[prostitute]].

